Workspace attach/routing/session/sync correctness plus global plugin adapters.

Adds the workspace correctness slice needed by kfactory:

  - opencode attach --workspace propagates through the attach command into
    packages/tui's SDKProvider and ProjectProvider.
  - validateSession honors the selected workspace.
  - workspace-routing middleware reads x-opencode-workspace for all methods,
    not only ?workspace= (one selector serves the v1 and /api/ paths).
  - Session.list and the service listGlobal use workspace_id as the primary
    scope when a workspace is explicit.
  - /experimental/session forwards ?workspace= into listGlobal.
  - /sync/start?workspace= targets the exact workspace after restart.
  - plugin workspace adapters register globally and lookup falls back to
    ProjectV2.ID.global while preserving project-specific overrides.
  - workspace lifecycle correctness: create-failure deletes the
    just-inserted row; remove() runs the adapter fail-closed FIRST.

This patch contains no kfactory-specific glue; see
opencode-kfactory-refresh.patch for the auth-cache layer applied on top.

